title: New head of AFRL space vehicles looking for talent to help push technology forward

title: NASA Waves Off First Artemis I Launch Attempt
summary: Following the Artemis I launch scrub Monday from Launch Complex 39B at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida, the agency will hold a media briefing at approximately 1 p.m. EDT today, Monday, Aug. 29, to discuss mission status.

title: First Artemis 1 launch attempt scrubbed
summary: NASA scrubbed the first attempt to launch its Space Launch System rocket and Orion spacecraft Aug. 29 after a problem with a hydrogen bleed line with one of the rocket’s four core stage engines.
